comments: Beal (WAS) reaches for the ball and marginal contact occurs with Mitchell (CLE) before starting his dribble.
Kuzma (WAS) legally contests Mitchell?s (CLE) jump shot attempt.
Mobley (CLE) engages with Beal (WAS) and releases from the marginal contact as he pursues the rebound.
Beal (WAS) initiates contact with Mobley?s (CLE) arm/elbow, which affects his play at the basket.
Porzingis (WAS) firms up and does not step into LeVert?s (CLE) path or deliver illegal contact on the hand-off pick.
Wright (WAS) and LeVert (CLE) mutually engage and disengage as marginal contact occurs during the inbound.
Porzingis (WAS) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an opponent.

Replay review of the foul called on Kuzma (WAS) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Mobley (CLE) goes to and not through Kuzma (WAS), who goes to the ground in an attempt to draw attention to the contact and makes leg to leg contact with Mobley, which affects his SQBR.
Allen (CLE) jumps alongside Beal (WAS) and avoids contact with his body during the play at the basket.
Mobley (CLE) establishes his right foot as his pivot and maintains it after gathering the ball.
Mitchell (CLE) engages with Beal (WAS) off-ball and marginal contact occurs as Mitchell releases away to retrieve the pass.
Osman (CLE) establishes himself in Beal?s (WAS) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Beal (WAS) swipes down and initiates contact with Mitchell?s (CLE) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Beal (WAS) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Mitchell (CLE) prior to incidental follow-through arm contact occurring on the steal.
Mobley (CLE) jumps into and initiates body contact with Beal (WAS), which affects his shot attempt near the rim.
Allen (CLE) establishes himself in Beal?s (WAS) path and his legs remain within the frame of his body as contact occurs, which he does not deliver.
Barton (WAS) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Mitchell (CLE) prior to incidental follow-through contact occurring on the steal attempt.
Mitchell (CLE) stops his forward momentum and marginal contact occurs with Wright (WAS) as he releases from the contact to gather on his jump shot attempt.
Beal (WAS) and Osman (CLE) come together as they simultaneously grab the loose ball and incidental contact occurs during the rebound.
Mitchell (CLE) gathers the ball on his right foot and takes more than two steps before elevating on his shot attempt.
Wright (WAS) reaches for the ball and marginal contact occurs as he brushes Mitchell's (CLE) arm before he starts his dribble drive toward the basket.
Barton (WAS) makes clean ball contact on his dislodge attempt after Mitchell (CLE) gathers on his driving shot attempt.
Kuzma (WAS) jumps from point A to point B and makes contact with Mitchell (CLE), which affects his driving shot attempt.
Wade (CLE) is established in Beal?s (WAS) path and absorbs the marginal body contact as they come together, prior to Beal throwing an errant pass.
Kuzma (WAS) initiates body contact by extending his forearm to Osman's (CLE) back, which affects his shot attempt near the rim.
Prior to the throw-in's release, Allen (CLE) grabs Porzingis (WAS) by the shoulder and is correctly whistled for an away from the play foul.
Porzingis' (WAS) pass ricochets off of the basket padding underneath the backboard, which is still inbounds.
Allen (CLE) establishes himself in Wright?s (WAS) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Wright (WAS) contests the driving shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Mitchell?s (CLE) arm after the release.
LeVert (CLE) moves into and delivers body contact to Beal (WAS), which affects Beal?s (WAS) SQBR during the drive.
Porzingis (WAS) grasps and then quickly releases Allen?s (CLE) jersey.
Porzingis (WAS) reaches for the ball and brushes Allen?s (CLE) arm as marginal contact occurs during Allen?s shot attempt near the rim.
LeVert (CLE) is moving in the same direction as Beal (WAS) when he immediately slides his hand off of Beal?s side and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Osman (CLE) legally contests Barton?s (WAS) jump shot attempt.
Porzingis (WAS) commits a take foul on Mitchell (CLE). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
LeVert (CLE) legally contests Porzingis? (WAS) jump shot attempt.
Barton (WAS) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds. Possession is correctly awarded to the Cavaliers.
